Regex Builder

- meta chars: {(, ), *, +, |, \, concat}
- input chars: {any char possible}
- ignore char: \ just ignore the next meta char behind it

building algorithm:

recommend_concat = false

if meta char:
	if ignore char:
		getnextchar
		push(char)
		if recommend_concat:
			push concat
		recommend_concat = true
	else:
		if char = *:
			eval if presendence
			push *
			recommend_concat = true
		else if char = +:
			eval if presendence
			push +
			recommend_concat = true
		else if char = |:
			eval if presendence
			push |
			if recommend_concat:
				recommend_concat = false
		else if char = (:
			if recommend_concat:
				push concat
			push (
		else if char = ):
			eval if presendence
			pop (
			recommend_concat = true
else:
	push(char)
	if recommend_concat:
		push concat
	recommend_concat = true

while operators is not empty:
	eval

set last state to final state
return nfa


testing:
- abc
- a|b
- a|bc
- a*c
- a*|b
- a*c+
- (a*|b)(b*|a)
- (abc)
- (a|b|c)+(b|a)*

concat inspection:
- a!b!c
- a|b
- a|b!c
- a*!c
- a*|b
- a*!c+
- (a*|b)!(b*|a)
- (a!b!c)
- (a|b|c)+!(b|a)*

concat rule:
if found a char or a single structure such as *, +, (), and the next thing is note | then add concat